Description: Save time and money by preventing, finding, and fixing IoT vulnerabilities before they cause harm.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: Internet-of-things (IoT) devices are rapidly growing in number and impact. These devices affect all aspects of life from our homes to the stability of our power grid and medical systems. Though the proliferation of IoT creates new opportunities, it also creates new targets and introduces risks for consumers and businesses. In particular, devices which previously had small footprints and limited capabilities now have broad attack surfaces; vulnerabilities in them may impact human trust, safety, and security. Current methods to secure embedded devices are complex and ineffective. Both the makers and purchasers of devices must have verifiable information to trust their security. Pilot Security automates this process, uncovering security vulnerabilities about all aspects of IoT device operations. The technology uses advanced automated analytic techniques we developed over years of manual cybersecurity reverse engineering combined with large public vulnerability databases to identify the most pressing security issues, inform the user, and provide actionable recommendations on remediation.
Industry Groups: Hardware, Information Technology, Privacy and Security, Science and Engineering, Software

Description: Hills & Vines Records Studio, Band, School.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Hills & Vines Records is a music production studio, band, and academy located in Boston, Massachusetts. The company was founded by Lead Rockie on July 12, 2022, and is known for producing premium audio songs for artists such as Karitas Kario, Aida Vee, Angela Kalule, and Saava Karim. The Hills & Vines Band made its debut performance on Valentine's Day at the French Club Waltham. The African-Jazz, contemporary live band is composed of Lead Rockie (Charles Baluku), Bruno 'Semax' Semanda (vocalist), Karitas Kario (vocalist), Eric Wabulo (drummer), and Amanda Nassirye (vocalist). The band has worked with numerous notable musicians, including Bobi Wine, Julius Kakembo, George Mulindwa, and many more. Hills & Vines Records is set to launch the Hills & Vines Academy, a music academy that aims to recognize, improve, and develop music skills in both adults and minors. Our music recording studio and band company, Hills & Vines Records, is dedicated to helping artists of all genres bring their musical visions to life. Located in the heart of Waltham, Boston, our state-of-the-art recording studio is equipped with the latest technology and staffed by a team of experienced engineers and producers. Whether you're a solo artist or part of a band, we have the tools and expertise to help you create a professional-quality recording. In addition to our recording services, we also offer a variety of band services, including rehearsals, performance coaching, and booking assistance. We have a team of talented musicians on staff who are available to join your band as session players or to help you put together a lineup for a one-time event. At Hills & Vines Records, we believe that every artist should have the opportunity to pursue their passion, and we strive to make our services accessible and affordable. We offer flexible scheduling and competitive pricing to make sure that your project stays within your budget. In addition to our services, we also host a variety of events at our studio, music industry workshops, and live concerts featuring local and touring acts. These events are open to the public and provide a platform for artists to connect and collaborate. At Hills & Vines, our goal is to help musicians at every stage of their career achieve their goals and bring their music to a wider audience. We look forward to working with you and helping you bring your musical dreams to life.
